📘 C. Schedule Management —
🔥 1. Problem Summary
n workers, m tasks
Each task has a preferred worker
Time:
Preferred worker → 1 hour
Other worker → 2 hours

👉 Goal:

Minimize the time when all tasks are completed
🧠 2. Key Insight

👉 Workers work in parallel
👉 So total time =

maximum time taken by any worker
⚡ 3. Core Idea

👉 We guess time = T and check:

Can all workers finish all tasks within time T?

👉 If YES → try smaller T
👉 If NO → increase T

✔️ Binary Search on Answer

🧩 4. Data Representation
vector<ll> t(n);

👉 t[i] = number of tasks worker i is proficient in

🔍 5. Feasibility Function
bool pos(time)

👉 Check if all tasks can be completed in given time

🔹 For each worker:
Case 1: Enough own tasks
if(t[i] >= time)

👉 Worker can do time tasks (all preferred)

Case 2: Not enough own tasks
else {
    // do all own tasks
    total -= t[i];

    // use remaining time for others
    total -= (time - t[i]) / 2;
}

👉 Explanation:

Remaining time = time - t[i]
Each extra task takes 2 hours
🔹 Final Check
if(total <= 0) return true;

👉 All tasks completed

🚀 6. Binary Search
ll l = 0, r = 2*m;

👉 Worst case: all tasks take 2 hours

while(l <= r)
If possible → move left
Else → move right
💻 7. Code
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
#define ll long long

bool pos(ll time, vector<ll>& t, ll total) {
    for(int i = 0; i < t.size(); i++) {

        if(t[i] >= time) {
            total -= time;
        } 
        else {
            total -= t[i];
            total -= (time - t[i]) / 2;
        }

        if(total <= 0) return true;
    }
    return false;
}

void solve() {
    ll n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;

    vector<ll> t(n);

    for(int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        ll w;
        cin >> w;
        w--;
        t[w]++;
    }

    ll l = 0, r = 2*m;
    ll ans = r;

    while(l <= r) {
        ll mid = (l + r) / 2;

        if(pos(mid, t, m)) {
            ans = mid;
            r = mid - 1;
        }
        else {
            l = mid + 1;
        }
    }

    cout << ans << endl;
}

int main() {
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}
🧠 8. Intuition Summary

👉 Each worker has time budget = T

They:

Do own tasks (fast → 1 hr)
Help others (slow → 2 hr)

👉 Check if total work done ≥ m

⚠️ 9. Common Mistakes

❌ Trying greedy assignment
❌ Simulating tasks directly
❌ Forgetting extra tasks take 2 hours
❌ Not using binary search

🔥 10. Pattern Recognition

Whenever you see:

Minimize maximum time
Parallel workers
Different speeds

👉 Think:

Binary Search on Answer + Feasibility Check
⚡ 11. One-Line Summary

Guess time and check if workers can complete all tasks within that time.
